- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is also likely because the paper discusses software transactional memory and hybrid transactional memory, which are programming language constructs. 
- cs.AR (Architecture) is a possibility because the paper discusses hardware transactional memory and its implementation on specific architectures (Intel and IBM POWER8). 
- cs.OS (Operating Systems) is a possibility because the paper discusses the implementation of transactional memory systems, which may interact with the operating system. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a possibility because the paper discusses the design and optimization of transactional memory algorithms.
